# L2-DEC-016 ambiguous-detection fixture.
#
# Two records hand-crafted to score IRIG = Standard = 4 across the
# L2-DEC-015 probe. Per the L2-DEC-016 classifier this lands in the
# AMBIGUOUS bucket (margin = 0 is below MIN_MARGIN = 3).
#
# Each record's Type Word declares word_count = 8 (raw 0x0802, LE
# bytes 02 08), so the record length matches the actual 16 bytes in
# the hex below. This is important: if the declared word_count
# disagreed with the actual byte layout, find_first_record's
# look-ahead would land on filler bytes mid-record and reject the
# candidate via the wrong code path (MieNoValidRecords instead of
# the L2-DEC-016 MieTimestampFormatMismatch we are trying to
# exercise).
#
# Per-record scoring breakdown:
#   * Type Word 0x0802: message_type = 0x02 (BC_TO_RT), wc = 8.
#     Inside the T/R-sensitive set, so a Receive-direction Cmd Word
#     at either candidate offset (offset+6 Standard, offset+8 IRIG)
#     scores +2.
#   * IRIG Cmd at offset+8: raw 0x0000. Direction = Receive
#     (matches BC_TO_RT) -> +2 IRIG. data_word_count = 0,
#     wc - 6 = 2, no match -> no IRIG WC bonus.
#   * Standard Cmd at offset+6: raw 0x0000. Direction = Receive ->
#     +2 Standard. data_word_count = 0, wc - 5 = 3, no match -> no
#     Standard WC bonus.
#   * IRIG TS fields deliberately out of range:
#       ts_upper = 0x001F  (hour = 31, > 23)
#       ts_middle = 0xFFFF (minute = 63, > 59)
#     -> no IRIG range bonus.
#
# Total per record: IRIG +2 / Standard +2. Over 2 records the
# aggregate is IRIG 4 / Standard 4. max_score = 4 doesn't reach
# DECISIVE_FLOOR = 8 AND margin = 0 < MIN_MARGIN = 3 -> AMBIGUOUS.
#
# Byte 12 (record 1) and byte 28 (record 2) differ so the L2-SYN-018
# homogeneous-payload defense doesn't fire (consecutive records are
# not byte-identical in non-timestamp positions).
0208 1F00 FFFF 0000 0000 0000 0100 0000
0208 1F00 FFFF 0000 0000 0000 0200 0000
